Functions implement saveflags and load flags that read the users arguments and either load the previously saved map, or save the current map. Or both at the same time.

save dungeon creates a unsigned char array that represents the dungeon map as provided in assignment specification, and saves it to disk

load dungeon looks for a saved dungeon and loads it into a unsigned char array and recreates the dungeon based on that.

If no file is found or invalid file, just creates a random dungeon 

Get game directory method constructs a directory based on the home directory and /.rlg327 

get game file name appends dungeon onto the game directory 


